rComments: You don't want to miss his class. He gives you the most elaborate information. Very powerful! Handsome too!I didn't want to leave his class!I just wanted to listen to him!

The midterm was easy because we were given the test questions and answers the week before the test. However, approx. 60% of the grade was assigned in the last 2 days, so there was no mark breakdown. My mark (as well as those of my peers) plummeted (89% on midterm; 75% in course) and Fatemi was useless in explaining why.

This class is chill. Prof is alright, needs to be more organized though. I would prefer if he were to post his lecture slides online before class. Also, the syllabus did include due dates.  And he tested us on stuff he didn't actually cover. Don't take this class if you're too shy to talk in class, participation is worth too much to gamble with.

I don't know why people said his tests were easy, because they are not. Most of the questions seemed irrelevant and had nothing to do with the lectures or readings. Spent too much time on "mindfulness" and not enough time actually learning. "Class participation" seemed like a waste of time. On the bright side he's a nice guy :)
Excellent Course! I loved this prof. Lectures were both educational and inspiring... But I hated how everybody in my class would ask stupid questions just to get a participation mark.
